===Etymology===
First used by U.S. President Ronald Reagan to describe weak enemies fighting individually or in small, underground groups for their homeland in the Near and Middle East, particularly Palestinians.


===Noun===
# Someone, or a unique group of any size, in a violent power struggle who does not engage a superior force in a formal or traditional battle but attacks an Achilles' heal for maximum damage at minimum cost. Also know as a Gorilla in Gorilla Warfare.

# Someone who uses terror as a weapon in a (usually violent) political struggle, typically in an attempt to coerce a more powerful opponent, such as a government.  Formerly, someone who governs by terror, as in "The Terror" of the French revolution.

